body:
Azure integration uses modern Azure SDK v5+ packages:

- @azure/arm-servicefabric: ARM management operations for SF clusters
- @azure/servicefabric: Service Fabric client APIs for cluster operations
- @azure/identity: ClientSecretCredential for authentication
- @azure/logger: Logging with setLogLevel and AzureLogger

Logging pattern in sfMgr.ts constructor:
```typescript
setLogLevel('verbose');
AzureLogger.log = (...args) => {
  SfUtility.outputLog(args.join(' '));
};
```

Use SfUtility.outputLog() for all diagnostic output to maintain consistent logging.

Credentials managed via SfExtSecrets class using VSCode SecretStorage API.
